As a native Floridian raised in a multi-cultural househo c.
I was surrounded by delicious homemade foods prepared
with love by Mom. So, it's no surprise that I would later
become a chef, passionate about nutritious, wholesome
and delicious foods.
I started my culinary career about 15 years ago at Johnson
and Wales University, and have worked at some of the
finest restaurants in the country.
Though most of my mentors and training have been
classically French, my palate is still somewhat Latin and
very much American. When it comes to creating recipes,
I believe less is more. I focus on freshness and seasonal
foods. I thoughtfully combine flavors that meld together
beautifully to give you a comforting dining experience
through luxurious ingredients. I strive to make people
happy and content while experiencing my cuisine. I hope
to make this journey a pleasant one for you.
Thank you for choosing Delta's BusinessElite so that I can
express my gratitude in every bite you take.
Chef Michelle Bernstein
Welcome Aboard
Welcome aboard Delta's BusinessElite®, where your need for convenience,
comfort and premium service is recognized. We invite you to sit back and enjoy
a variety of international flavors designed for your pleasure. To complement
your meal and enhance your dining enjoyment, we are proud to suggest
a wine from our award-winning collection. Please ask your flight attendant
for today's featured selections.
Thank you for choosing Delta's BusinessElite.
Ideal Pertormance Meals
Delta has partnered with Human Performance Institute to develop choices
which help travelers on board and upon arrival.
Look for this symbol if you plan to work on board. These meals will
keep you alert now and allow you to rest upon landing.
This symbol denotes choices which will help you to rest on board
and be alert for meetings you may have upon arrival.
To arrive refreshed at your destination, Delta recommends drinking plenty
of water and moving around every hour or so. Setting your watch to the
new time zone and adapting to local eating and sleeping habits will also
enhance your comfort.
For more information, contact training and nutrition specialists
Human Performance Institute at 407-438-9911
or www.energyforperformance.com
